HEADWORD: decollate
<hw>de*col"late</hw> <pr>(d⟦esl⟧*k⟦ocr⟧l"l⟦amac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Decollated</conjf>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Decollating</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[L. <ets>decollatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>decollare</ets> to behead;
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>collum</ets> neck.]</ety> <def>To sever from the
neck; to behead; to decapitate.</def>⟦br⟧
